SUMMARY:Jaaji
DESCRIPTION:‘Help\, I’m shrinking!’ \nJaaji always follows her heart. She is tall\, strong\, and brave: a woman who knows exactly what her elephants need and does what needs to be done. \nThen she meets Max. And slowly\, without noticing\, she does whatever Max likes. She becomes small\, weak\, fearful. She neglects her giants. \nA play in both English and Kannada\, her story is told through live music\, masks\, Muppets\, Bunraku-style puppets\, and finger puppets. A playful\, colourful theatre performance for young audiences and adults alike\, Jaaji invites you to celebrate your own shape\, size\, and courage. \nCredits:\nProducer: Namkampani\nDirector: Gerti Tröbinger\nPuppet Design: Gerti Tröbinger\nDramaturge: Padmavati Rao\nPerformers: Surabhi Vasisht\, Trishala Srinivas\nAssistant Director: Mrinali Chouhan\nMusic Composition: M D Pallavi\nLyrics: Shashank Rajashekar\nPercussions: Raghavendra K\nLight Design: Subodha Subrahmanya\nPublicity Design: Deepthi Prasad\nExecutive Producer: Priti Bakalkar\nSpace Support: Shoonya Centre for Art and Somatic Practices \nIn collaboration with:\n \nSupported by:\n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/jaaji/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Theatre,Young BIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thumbnail_J2.jpg
END:VEVENT
